<h1>Choosing Between Two Items</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N1{{}}@HI{{to}}@N2{{}}@HI{{dochiraga}} <em>adjective</em> @HI{{desuka.}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
This question lists two items, @N1{{}} and @N2{{}}, and asks the listener to select the "more" <em>adjective</em> of the pair.
The interrogative @HI{{dochira}} is used because two items are presented. Note that @HI{{to}} follows <em>each</em> of the nouns
involved.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{north^sea^road-way}}to@KJ{{large^heights}}todochiraga@KJ{{refreshing}}shiidesuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Which is cooler, Hokkaido or Osaka?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/><br/>

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{mira-}}santo@KT{{santosu}}santodochiraga@KT{{tenisu}}ga@KJ{{above^hand}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Who is the better tennis player, Mr. Miller or Mr. Santos?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<br/><br/>
</p>

